{"type":"message","id":"fd5d3ffa","parentId":"a6e47232","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:41:40.983Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1378\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"1377\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-06 17:41 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Long ago in France, a boy named Louis lost his sight at age five.\\nHe wanted to read like everyone else but couldn't feel regular books.\\nAt twelve, he learned about soldiers' night writing using raised dots in the dark.\\nLouis thought he could make a simpler system for blind people to read.\\nHe worked hard, poking dots in paper with a special tool, trying many patterns.\\nFinally, he created six dots that could make every letter - the Braille system.\\nHis invention lets millions of blind people read and learn today.\\nLouis shows us that even a young person can change the world with determination.\\nGoodnight, sweet dreams, and remember you can do amazing things too.\\n🌙🖤\"\n}\n```\n\nTell another indian short story"}],"timestamp":1775497300970}}
{"type":"message","id":"33f69fcd","parentId":"fd5d3ffa","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:41:47.169Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I'll read the story that was previously shared to understand the context and then tell another Indian short story as requested. First, let me check the conversation context.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I'll tell you an Indian short story about Birbal, one of Emperor Akbar's wisest advisors.\n\nOnce, Akbar drew a line on the floor and asked his courtiers to make it shorter without touching it. Everyone was puzzled - how could you shorten a line without touching it? \n\nBirbal simply smiled, picked up a piece of chalk, and drew a longer line next to it. \"Your line is now shorter compared to mine,\" he said. \n\nAkbar laughed and praised Birbal's clever thinking. The moral? Sometimes changing your perspective makes the impossible possible.\n\nWant another one? 😊"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":22933,"output":208,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23141,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775497300982,"responseId":"gen-1775497301-vp94aAb4ugcgJ6sfPjAN"}}
{"type":"message","id":"39776b0d","parentId":"33f69fcd","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:42:25.071Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1380\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"1379\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-06 17:42 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"I'll tell you an Indian short story about Birbal, one of Emperor Akbar's wisest advisors.\\n\\nOnce, Akbar drew a line on the floor and asked his courtiers to make it shorter without touching it. Everyone was puzzled - how could you shorten a line without touching it?\\n\\nBirbal simply smiled, picked up a piece of chalk, and drew a longer line next to it. \\\"Your line is now shorter compared to mine,\\\" he said.\\n\\nAkbar laughed and praised Birbal's clever thinking. The moral? Sometimes changing your perspective makes the impossible possible.\\n\\nWant another one? 😊\"\n}\n```\n\nAnother one"}],"timestamp":1775497345058}}
{"type":"message","id":"3c361484","parentId":"39776b0d","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:42:39.038Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Okay, I need to tell another Indian short story. Let me think of a good one that's appropriate for a group chat. How about the story of Tenali Rama and the brinjal curry? That's a classic and funny one.\n\nActually, let me recall a different one - the story about the clever thief and Akbar. No, wait, let me do Tenali Rama since it's lighthearted and fun.\n\nTenali Rama was known for his wit in the Vijayanagara empire. There's a great story about how he once outsmarted some jealous courtiers.\n\nLet me share that one...\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"Here's another favorite - the story of Tenali Rama and the jealous courtiers:\n\nTenali Rama was so clever that some courtiers grew jealous and complained to King Krishnadevaraya that he got special treatment. The king decided to test them all.\n\nHe announced: \"Whoever can stay underwater the longest will win 1000 gold coins.\"\n\nThe courtiers took turns, managing only a minute or two each. When it was Tenali Rama's turn, he jumped in... and stayed underwater for nearly half an hour!\n\nEveryone was amazed. The king asked how he did it. Tenali Rama smiled and said, \"Your Majesty, I held a reed to breathe through while staying submerged.\"\n\nThe courtiers objected - \"That's cheating!\" But Tenali Rama replied, \"Is it? You asked who could stay underwater longest - not who could hold their breath longest!\"\n\nThe king laughed, rewarded Tenali Rama, and told the courtiers: \"Sometimes the wisest answer isn't the obvious one - it's the one that follows the rules while thinking beyond them.\"\n\nMoral: Look for creative solutions within the boundaries given. 😉\n\nWant one more? Or shall we save some for another time?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"kilocode","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b:free","usage":{"input":23370,"output":519,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23889,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775497345070,"responseId":"gen-1775497345-PJZPkX6Kph25i1Y0jl74"}}
{"type":"message","id":"7787b720","parentId":"3c361484","timestamp":"2026-04-06T17:43:59.155Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"1382\",\n  \"reply_to_id\": \"1381\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"conversation_label\": \"Nrexya id:-1003606834639\",\n  \"sender\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-04-06 17:43 UTC\",\n  \"group_subject\": \"Nrexya\",\n  \"is_group_chat\": true,\n  \"was_mentioned\": true,\n  \"has_reply_context\": true\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Nemesis (7924461837)\",\n  \"id\": \"7924461837\",\n  \"name\": \"Nemesis\",\n  \"username\": \"nemesis0008\"\n}\n```\n\nReplied message (untrusted, for context):\n```json\n{\n  \"sender_label\": \"Nexaaa\",\n  \"body\": \"Here's another favorite - the story of Tenali Rama and the jealous courtiers:\\n\\nTenali Rama was so clever that some courtiers grew jealous and complained to King Krishnadevaraya that he got special treatment. The king decided to test them all.\\n\\nHe announced: \\\"Whoever can stay underwater the longest will win 1000 gold coins.\\\"\\n\\nThe courtiers took turns, managing only a minute or two each. When it was Tenali Rama's turn, he jumped in... and stayed underwater for nearly half an hour!\\n\\nEveryone was amazed. The king asked how he did it. Tenali Rama smiled and said, \\\"Your Majesty, I held a reed to breathe through while staying submerged.\\\"\\n\\nThe courtiers objected - \\\"That's cheating!\\\" But Tenali Rama replied, \\\"Is it? You asked who could stay underwater longest - not who could hold their breath longest!\\\"\\n\\nThe king laughed, rewarded Tenali Rama, and told the courtiers: \\\"Sometimes the wisest answer isn't the obvious one - it's the one that follows the rules while thinking beyond them.\\\"\\n\\nMoral: Look for creative solutions within the boundaries given. 😉\\n\\nWant one more? Or shall we save some for another time?\"\n}\n```\n\nGn nexu"}],"timestamp":1775497439142}}
